com.tinkerpop.pipes.filter

Interface FilterPipe<S>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<S>, Iterator<S>, Pipe<S,S>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AndFilterPipe, BackFilterPipe, CollectionFilterPipe, CyclicPathFilterPipe, DuplicateFilterPipe, ExceptFilterPipe, FilterFunctionPipe, FutureFilterPipe, IdFilterPipe, IntervalFilterPipe, LabelFilterPipe, ObjectFilterPipe, OrFilterPipe, PropertyFilterPipe, RandomFilterPipe, RangeFilterPipe, RetainFilterPipe

    public interface FilterPipe<S>
extends Pipe<S,S>
    A FilterPipe has no specified behavior save that it takes the same objects it emits. This interface is used to specify that a Pipe will either emit its input or not.
    Author:
    Marko A. Rodriguez (http://markorodriguez.com)
